Collections are arranged into groups for searching. Click on a group name to search the collections in that group. A collection may include some content outside of the group's definition, and a collection could appear in more than one group. Click the title of a specific collection to search it alone. Sometimes it is advantageous to search a single collection. For example, search field and sorting options are often specific to the collection, allowing for a more refined search.

Some collections have a very narrow focus. Other collections are broader, and may encompass many sub-collections. Occassionally an image appears in multiple collections, though generally there is a single authoritative source for each image.

item.p: Matching words: The search engine attempts to match any word or phrase exactly as you put it in the box.
e.g.: Picasso and Rembrandt in a box will look for
Punctuation: All punctuation is treated as an empty space.
Case: The search engine is not case sensitive.
Wildcards: Use wildcard * to expand word stems. This is a good way to search for variations on a word.
Choose image collections: Limit your search to only those collections you choose in the image collections list.

Facets.Query: SELECT SQL_CALC_FOUND_ROWS * FROM ( SELECT t1.* FROM ( select istruct_isentryid, concat('S-sclaudubon-X-',sclaudubon_media.m_id,']',sclaudubon_media.m_iid ) as `id` , `istruct_caption_image_title` as `sortval` from sclaudubon left join sclaudubon_media on sclaudubon.ic_id = sclaudubon_media.m_id where ( ( match (`istruct_caption_image_title`) against ('American' in boolean mode) ) ) And sclaudubon_media.m_searchable = '1' ) t1, ItemBrowse f1 WHERE f1.idno = t1.istruct_isentryid AND f1.field = 'medium' AND f1.value = 'Lithograph' ) x1

SELECT* FROM ( SELECT t1.* FROM ( select istruct_isentryid, concat('S-sclaudubon-X-',sclaudubon_media.m_id,']',sclaudubon_media.m_iid ) as `id` , `istruct_caption_image_title` as `sortval` from sclaudubon left join sclaudubon_media on sclaudubon.ic_id = sclaudubon_media.m_id where ( ( match (`istruct_caption_image_title`) against ('American' in boolean mode) ) ) And sclaudubon_media.m_searchable = '1' ) t1, ItemBrowse f1 WHERE f1.idno = t1.istruct_isentryid AND f1.field = 'medium' AND f1.value = 'Lithograph' ) x1

SELECT b.field, b.value, COUNT(b.value) AS total FROM ItemBrowse b, ( SELECT* FROM ( SELECT t1.* FROM ( select istruct_isentryid, concat('S-sclaudubon-X-',sclaudubon_media.m_id,']',sclaudubon_media.m_iid ) as `id` , `istruct_caption_image_title` as `sortval` from sclaudubon left join sclaudubon_media on sclaudubon.ic_id = sclaudubon_media.m_id where ( ( match (`istruct_caption_image_title`) against ('American' in boolean mode) ) ) And sclaudubon_media.m_searchable = '1' ) t1, ItemBrowse f1 WHERE f1.idno = t1.istruct_isentryid AND f1.field = 'medium' AND f1.value = 'Lithograph' ) x1 ) a WHERE b.collid = ? AND a.istruct_isentryid = b.idno GROUP BY b.field, b.value ORDER BY b.field, total DESC, b.value
